---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';
---
<Layout title="Privacy Policy" description="VoiceCloser privacy policy - how we collect, use, and protect your personal data.">
  <div class="legal-page">
    <h1>Privacy Policy</h1>
    <p class="legal-updated">Last updated: March 21, 2026</p>

    <p>Welcome to VoiceCloser ("VoiceCloser," "we," "us," "our"), operated by RECO QA LLC. VoiceCloser provides AI-powered voice agent services through its website at voicecloser.io (the "Site") and its related platform, applications, and services (collectively, the "Services"). This Privacy Policy describes how we collect, use, and protect information from users of the Services ("you," "your").</p>

    <h2>Information We Collect</h2>

    <h3>Information You Provide</h3>
    <p>We collect personal information you voluntarily provide when you:</p>
    <ul>
      <li>Create an account or register for the Services</li>
      <li>Fill out intake or onboarding forms</li>
      <li>Request a demo call or submit a form that includes SMS consent</li>
      <li>Contact us via email or other channels</li>
      <li>Subscribe to a paid plan</li>
    </ul>
    <p>This may include your name, email address, phone number, business name, payment information, and SMS consent preferences.</p>

    <h3>Information Collected Automatically</h3>
    <p>When you use the Services, we automatically collect certain information, including:</p>
    <ul>
      <li><strong>Usage data:</strong> pages visited, features used, timestamps, and interactions</li>
      <li><strong>Device data:</strong> browser type, operating system, IP address</li>
      <li><strong>Cookies:</strong> we use cookies and similar technologies to maintain sessions and analyze usage</li>
    </ul>

    <h3>Call and Voice Data</h3>
    <p>Our Services involve AI-powered voice agents that make and receive phone calls on your behalf. In connection with this, we may collect:</p>
    <ul>
      <li>Call recordings and transcripts</li>
      <li>Call metadata (duration, timestamps, phone numbers)</li>
      <li>Call analysis data (sentiment, summaries, outcomes)</li>
    </ul>
    <p>Call recordings and transcripts are stored securely and are accessible only to you and authorized personnel within your organization.</p>

    <h2>How We Use Your Information</h2>
    <p>We use the information we collect to:</p>
    <ul>
      <li>Provide, operate, and improve the Services</li>
      <li>Process transactions and manage your subscription</li>
      <li>Make and receive calls through our AI voice agents on your behalf</li>
      <li>Analyze call performance and provide reporting</li>
      <li>Send administrative communications (account updates, billing, security alerts)</li>
      <li>Respond to your inquiries and provide support</li>
      <li>Comply with legal obligations</li>
    </ul>
    <p>We do not sell your personal information to third parties.</p>

    <h2>SMS/Text Message Communications</h2>
    <p>VoiceCloser may send you SMS (text) messages related to your demo, account, or our services. This section explains how we collect consent, what messages you may receive, and how to opt out.</p>

    <h3>How We Obtain Consent</h3>
    <p>We obtain your consent to send SMS messages when you:</p>
    <ul>
      <li>Request a demo call through our website and check the SMS consent checkbox</li>
      <li>Submit a custom agent build form with SMS consent</li>
      <li>Book a consultation and provide your phone number with SMS consent</li>
      <li>Opt in to SMS notifications through your account settings</li>
    </ul>
    <p>Your consent is recorded with a timestamp and the specific context in which it was provided.</p>

    <h3>Types of Messages</h3>
    <p>You may receive the following types of SMS messages from VoiceCloser:</p>
    <ul>
      <li><strong>Demo follow-ups:</strong> Confirmation that your demo call was placed and follow-up messages related to your demo experience</li>
      <li><strong>Appointment reminders:</strong> Confirmations and reminders for scheduled strategy calls or support calls</li>
      <li><strong>Account notifications:</strong> Important updates about your account, subscription status, or security alerts</li>
      <li><strong>Marketing messages (if opted in):</strong> Product tips, workflow ideas, feature announcements, and exclusive offers</li>
    </ul>

    <h3>Message Frequency</h3>
    <p>Message frequency varies based on your interactions with our service. Typically:</p>
    <ul>
      <li>Demo follow-ups: 1–3 messages per demo request</li>
      <li>Appointment reminders: 1–3 messages per scheduled appointment</li>
      <li>Account notifications: Only when action is required (varies)</li>
      <li>Marketing messages: 1–2 per month (if opted in)</li>
    </ul>

    <h3>Carrier Charges</h3>
    <p>Message and data rates may apply. Standard messaging rates from your wireless carrier will apply to any SMS messages you receive. VoiceCloser does not charge separately for SMS messages, but your carrier may charge you for each message received. Contact your wireless carrier for details about your messaging plan.</p>

    <h3>Opting Out</h3>
    <p>You can opt out of SMS messages at any time by:</p>
    <ul>
      <li>Replying <strong>STOP</strong> to any SMS message you receive from us</li>
      <li>Visiting our <a href="/opt-out">opt-out page</a></li>
      <li>Contacting us at <a href="mailto:support@voicecloser.io">support@voicecloser.io</a></li>
    </ul>
    <p>After opting out, you will receive a confirmation message and no further SMS messages will be sent unless you re-subscribe. Opting out of SMS does not affect other communications (email, in-app notifications).</p>

    <h3>Getting Help</h3>
    <p>Reply <strong>HELP</strong> to any SMS message for assistance, or contact us at <a href="mailto:support@voicecloser.io">support@voicecloser.io</a>.</p>

    <h3>No Third-Party Sharing of SMS Consent</h3>
    <p>We do not sell, rent, or share your phone number or SMS consent with third parties for their marketing purposes. Your phone number and consent information will only be used by RECO QA LLC (VoiceCloser) and our service providers who assist in delivering SMS messages on our behalf. These service providers are contractually prohibited from using your information for any purpose other than providing SMS delivery services to us.</p>

    <h2>Third-Party Services</h2>
    <p>We use the following third-party services to operate the platform:</p>
    <ul>
      <li><strong>Retell AI:</strong> powers our voice agent technology, processes call audio and transcripts</li>
      <li><strong>Supabase:</strong> database and authentication infrastructure</li>
      <li><strong>Stripe:</strong> payment processing and subscription management</li>
      <li><strong>PostHog:</strong> product analytics and usage tracking</li>
    </ul>
    <p>Each of these providers has their own privacy policies and we only share the minimum information necessary for them to perform their functions.</p>

    <h2>Data Sharing and Disclosure</h2>
    <p>We do not sell, rent, or trade your personal information. We may share your information in the following limited circumstances:</p>
    <ul>
      <li><strong>Service providers:</strong> with third-party vendors who assist in operating the Services (as described above)</li>
      <li><strong>Legal requirements:</strong> when required by law, subpoena, or legal process</li>
      <li><strong>Protection of rights:</strong> to protect the rights, property, or safety of VoiceCloser, our users, or the public</li>
      <li><strong>Business transfers:</strong> in connection with a merger, acquisition, or sale of assets, your information may be transferred as part of that transaction</li>
    </ul>

    <h2>Data Security</h2>
    <p>We take reasonable measures to protect your personal information from unauthorized access, alteration, disclosure, or destruction. This includes encryption of data in transit and at rest, role-based access controls, and regular security reviews. However, no method of transmission over the Internet is 100% secure, and we cannot guarantee absolute security.</p>

    <h2>Data Retention</h2>
    <p>We retain your personal information for as long as your account is active or as needed to provide the Services. Call recordings and transcripts are retained for the duration of your subscription. Upon account deletion, we will remove your data within 30 days, except where retention is required by law.</p>

    <h2>Your Rights and Choices</h2>
    <p>Depending on your location, you may have the right to:</p>
    <ul>
      <li>Access the personal data we hold about you</li>
      <li>Request correction of inaccurate data</li>
      <li>Request deletion of your data</li>
      <li>Opt out of marketing communications</li>
      <li>Request a copy of your data in a portable format</li>
    </ul>
    <p>To exercise any of these rights, contact us at <a href="mailto:support@voicecloser.io">support@voicecloser.io</a>.</p>

    <h2>State-Specific Privacy Rights</h2>
    <p>Residents of states with consumer privacy laws (including California, Colorado, Connecticut, Virginia, and others) may have additional rights regarding their personal data, including the right to know what data is collected, request deletion, and opt out of data sales. We do not sell personal data. To make a request under your state's privacy law, email <a href="mailto:support@voicecloser.io">support@voicecloser.io</a>.</p>

    <h2>Children's Privacy</h2>
    <p>The Services are not intended for individuals under the age of 18. We do not knowingly collect personal information from children. If you believe a child has provided us with personal information, please contact us and we will promptly delete it.</p>

    <h2>Cookies</h2>
    <p>We use cookies and similar technologies to maintain your session, remember your preferences, and analyze how the Services are used. You can control cookies through your browser settings. Disabling cookies may limit your ability to use certain features of the Services.</p>

    <h2>Links to Other Websites</h2>
    <p>The Services may contain links to third-party websites. We are not responsible for the privacy practices of those websites. We encourage you to review their privacy policies before providing any personal information.</p>

    <h2>Changes to This Policy</h2>
    <p>We may update this Privacy Policy from time to time. If we make material changes, we will notify you by email or through the Services. Your continued use of the Services after any changes constitutes your acceptance of the updated policy.</p>

    <h2>Contact Us</h2>
    <p>If you have questions about this Privacy Policy or our data practices, contact us at:</p>
    <p><a href="mailto:support@voicecloser.io">support@voicecloser.io</a></p>
  </div>
</Layout>
